testcase.name: Invoking Podam on a POJO with a private, no arguments constructor, should return a non null POJO
Invoking Podam on a POJO with a circular constructor (e.g. java.net.URL) leads to a null POJO
Podam should fill in Maps of the containing class type
Podam should fill embedded abstract classes if a concrete type has been specified
Invoking Podam on an interface should return an empty POJO
Podam should fill in a POJO with basic jvm types
Podam should handle immutable POJOs annotated with @PodamConstructor
Invoking Podam on an Abstract class should return a null pojo
Podam should fill recursive POJOs when invoking the factory population directly
Podam should fill recursive POJOs correctly, including all their fields
Podam should fill POJOs with non default constructors
Podam should fill in lists of the containing class type
Podam should generate a non null POJO for Abstract types with a concrete type
Podam should fill in POJOs which have a circular dependency
Invoking Podam on a POJO with both circular and non circular constructors (e.g. javax.activation.DataHandler) should lead to a non empty POJO
